==Personal life==
When Saunders was born, his father [[Flip Saunders]] was an assistant coach at the [[Minnesota Golden Gophers men's basketball|University of Minnesota]].<ref name="Wizards Assistant Coaches | The Official site of the Washington Wizards">{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/wizards/assistantcoaches_091104.html |title=Wizards Assistant Coaches |publisher=NBA.com |accessdate=May 3, 2014 }}</ref> Ryan Saunders grew up in [[Wisconsin]] and [[South Dakota]], as Flip later worked as head coach for [[Continental Basketball Association|CBA]] teams in those states (specifically, the [[Rapid City Thrillers]] (1988–1989), [[La Crosse Catbirds]] (1989–1994), and [[Sioux Falls Skyforce]] (1994–1995)). In 1995, the Saunders family returned to the [[Minneapolis–Saint Paul]] area when Flip Saunders became head coach of the [[Minnesota Timberwolves]], a position he would maintain for the rest of Ryan's childhood.<ref>http://www.nba.com/coachfile/flip_saunders/index.html</ref>

Saunders married his wife Hayley in 2017. Their son Lucas Philip Saunders was born on June 6th, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fox9.com/sports/ryan-saunders-wife-welcome-baby-boy|title=Timberwolves head coach Ryan Saunders, wife welcome baby boy|last=FOX|website=KMSP|access-date=2019-07-06}}</ref> Lucas's middle name is a dedication to Ryan's father, the late [[Flip Saunders]].

Saunders has taken part in multiple basketball camps for the youth and charitable organizations in Minnesota.<ref>[http://www.nba.com/wizards/assistantcoaches_091104.html Wizards Assistant Coaches]</ref>

